{
  "prompt": "A concept design of a central-drive (mid-drive) EREV (Extended Range Electric Vehicle) motorcycle. The motorcycle has a compact 72V central electric motor positioned between the pedals or footrests. Below the seat and integrated into the frame is a 72V 40Ah prismatic battery pack. At the rear side of the vehicle (where the tail box would be), there is a small gasoline-powered generator mounted horizontally, with air vents and exhaust visible. The fuel tank is placed above the generator, holding about 3L of fuel. The overall frame is similar to a scooter or step-through motorcycle, with a clean and minimalistic design. The image should show labeled components like motor, battery, generator, fuel tank. Futuristic, clean, and technical rendering style. Side view.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
